est promotes our well-being.Accessible and lively, and drawing on perspectives from the humanities, religion, and the arts, as well as social science and the law, On Freedom explores a crucial dimension of the human condition that philosophers and economists have long missed-and shows what it would take to make freedom real.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aChoice (Psychology)xEconomic aspects. 0aCompulsive behaviorxPsychological aspects. 0aConduct of life. 0aHappiness. 0aSelf-controlxPsychological aspects. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Freedom.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691192024zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691192024423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691192024.jpg  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DSWb2019